# Variables & Declarations

## Use const and let

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - const for values that won't be reassigned
const user = getUser();
const items = [1, 2, 3];

// ✅ GOOD - let only when reassignment is needed
let count = 0;
count += 1;

// ❌ BAD - never use var
var name = 'test';
```

## One declaration per variable

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const foo = 1;
const bar = 2;

// ❌ BAD
const foo = 1, bar = 2;
```

## Group const and let

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - group const, then let
const userId = 1;
const name = 'John';
let isActive = false;
let count = 0;

// ❌ BAD - mixed declarations
let count = 0;
const userId = 1;
let isActive = false;
```

## No unused variables

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - unused variable
const unused = 'never used';

// ✅ GOOD - prefix with _ if intentionally unused
const [first, _second, third] = array;
```
